<chapter id="using-kphotobook">
<title>Using &kphotobook;</title>

<sect1 id="strength">
  <title>Strength of <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis></title>
  <para>The strength of <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> lies in its highly configurable but still easy to use tag tree. You can use this tag tree to easily annotate tags to your photos but also to filter and search the photos. There are several types of tags which gives you all the freedom you need to organize your photos in a way <emphasis>you</emphasis> want it to. Certainly the photos can also be filtered by their source folder. All your filtering wishes can also be combined! In this chapter we will show you how to use <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> and we will show you how to get the most out of the powerful tools. </para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="database">
  <title>The <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> database</title>
  <para>A <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> database is stored as one XML-file. This file contains all source folders, tags and files belonging to this database. Of course it is possible to have several databases storing different types of photos, if you wish.</para>
  <para>When a database has changed (tags or source folders were edited) the file must be saved. That means that changes are not automatically persisted. Each time a file is saved the old file is backed-up.</para>
</sect1>





<sect1 id="source_folders">
  <title>Source Directories</title>
    <para>The <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> database contains all images of one or more source folders. Source folders can be added recursively or not. For <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> it doesn't matter where on the hard drive your photos are stored. <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> can handle as many source folders as you wish. They can even be added recursively or not.</para>

    <sect2>
      <title>The Source Directory Tree</title>
      <para>The Source Directory Tree shows all the source folders which belong to the database. As known from Konqueror, folders with subfolders can be expanded and collapsed. There are some very handy operations which are accessible through the folder tree context menu:</para>
        <sect3>
        <title>Context Menu when Clicking <guimenu>Beside</guimenu> Folders:</title>

        <variablelist>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Include All</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Includes all source folders which are in the database to the preview</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Exclude All</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Excludes all source folders from the preview</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Invert All</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>All folders which were included to the preview will be excluded and vice versa</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Expand All</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>The folder Tree will be expanded. All source folders are visible</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Collapse all Source Directories</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>The folder tree will be collapsed. Only the top level folders are shown</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Add Source Directory</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Prompts the dialog to add a source folder (recursively or not)</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

        </variablelist>

    </sect3>


    <sect3>
        <title>Context Menu when Clicking <guimenu>On</guimenu> Folders:</title>

        <variablelist>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Include Whole Folder</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Includes the folder to the preview. Subfolders will be included as well</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Exclude Whole Folder</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Excludes the folder from the preview. Subfolders will be excluded as well</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Invert Folder Selection</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>All subfolders of the current folder which were included to the preview will be excluded and vice versa</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Expand Source Directory</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Expands the current folder</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
          <term><menuchoice>
          <guimenuitem>Collapse Source Directory</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice></term>
          <listitem><para><action>Collapses the current folder</action></para></listitem>
          </varlistentry>


        </variablelist>
      </sect3>

    </sect2>
    <sect2>
    <title>Adding Source Directories</title>
    <para>The <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> database contains all images of one ore more source folders. Source folders can be added recursively or not. Adding them recursively makes <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> add the selected folder and all folders below it. When adding a folder recursively, hard- and soft-links are followed by default. To prevent endless loops <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> tries to detect and suppress loops in the file system folder structure.</para>
      <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>non-recursive: only the files in the selected folder will be added to the database.</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>recursive: all files in the selected folder and all sub-folders will be added to the database.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>When restarting <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> every source folder will be rescanned by default. New found sub-folders and files will be added to the database. This function can also be executed manually. Missed folders or files will not automatically be removed from the database to prevent loss of the association between files and tags.</para>
    </sect2>

    <sect2>
    <title>Removing Source Directories</title>
    <para>Removing source folders will only remove the folder and all its files from the <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> database. No files will be deleted on your hard drive, however, you will lose all associations between the deleted photos and the tags associated with them.</para>
    </sect2>

    <sect2>
    <title>Rescan Source Directories</title>
    <para>Rescanning the source folder will check the source folders for new and deleted sub folders and files. New files and folders will automatically be added to the database. <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis> will ask for user input when folders and files are deleted.</para>
    </sect2>
</sect1>



<sect1 id="thumb_win">
  <title>Thumbnail Window</title>
  <para>The thumbnail window shows all the photos of your database... depending on your filter, of course. Filtering will be explained later on.</para>
    <sect2>
        <title>Thumbnail size</title>
        <para>The thumbnail size of the images can be changed. This can be done by the "View" menu, by the magnifiers or via the Settings --> Configure <emphasis>&kmyapplication;</emphasis>. The sizes are limited from a minimal size of 32 px to a maximal size of 160 px. In the configure dialog you can also set the font and font size of the filenames which are shown below the image previews.</para>

