    <sect3>
        <title>Deleting Tags</title>
        <para>Tags can be deleted via the Tag context menu. Click with the right mouse button on the Tag you want to delete and chose the entry "Delete Tag". The Tag and the associations between the Tag and the photos will be deleted. If you delete a Tag which contains Sub Tags, the Sub Tags and their associations to the photos will also be deleted.</para>
    </sect3>

    <sect3>
        <title>Editing Tags</title>
        <para>Tags can be edited via the Tag context menu. There you can edit the Tags Name, Comment and Icon. You cannot edit the tag type though. The Name of the Tag is what represents the Tag in the Tag tree. The comment you can set will be shown as a tool tip of this tag when hovering over it. If you select an icon, it will show left beside the Tag name in the tag tree. Choosing no icon will not show any icon at all (no space holder). </para>
    </sect3>

