<chapter id="kpb_configuration">
  <title>Configuring &kmyapplication;</title>
  <para> Many aspects of &kmyapplication; can be altered in the configure dialog. We will take you through all the options in this chapter.</para>

  <sect1 id="config_dialog">
    <title>The Configure Dialog</title>
    <para>&kmyapplication; can be configured at "Settings" --> "Configure KPhotoBook". The configute dialog is split up in six parts which hold the options for special aspects of the program. The button "Defaults" will reset all options of all parts to the default values. "OK" will apply the changes and close the dialog. "Apply" will apply the changes and keep the dialog open. "Cancel" will deny the changes and close the dialog.</para>

